tlt_video on Instagram: "Hi!
How are you preparing for your trip to Japan?
This content is a report on recommended restaurants from a Japanese perspective and tips for traveling in Japan.
The name of the restaurant I will introduce this time is "gallery11".
As the name suggests, the interior is decorated with artistic decorations, and the view from the 11th floor is wonderful.
Rooftop restaurants are rare in Japan, and this restaurant's location will become more crowded as it becomes more well-known.
In fact, the terrace seats were closed due to heavy rain until just before we took our photos, but we received special permission from the restaurant to take the photos.
*Normally, you can eat meals on the terrace seats.
There is also a special BBQ plan for the terrace seats, so please check it out when you visit.
The dishes are mainly Mediterranean, so you can choose from a wide variety of colorful dishes.

And this time, I ordered:
・2 glasses of wine
・1 plate of hors d'oeuvres
・1 plate of pasta
・1 small-sized main BBQ plate

I think the total was US$81.25, which is relatively reasonable.
This restaurant can accommodate families with children and large groups, and the staff are very friendly, so don't worry.
And there are staff who are fluent in English, so don't worry. 
※Only restaurant patrons can enter this terrace.
I hope this will be a hint for your trip to Japan.
Have a good trip. 👋

🏬gallery11
📲@gallery11shibuya
📍11/F Hotel Indigo Tokyo, 2-25-12 Dogenzaka, Shibuya-ku, Tokyo

⚫︎Business hours: Lunch 11:00-23:00, Dinner 18:00-21:30.
⚫︎Closed: None.
⚫︎Payment method: Cash, credit card.
⚫︎Location: About 10 minutes walk from each Shibuya station.
⚫︎Reservations: Reservations are recommended.
⚫︎Entry attributes: 1 person, couples, families, large groups,all🆗.
⚫︎Staff service: Excellent.
※Infants are also welcome.
